This article provides a transcript of remarks made by UK Prime Minister Theresa May and US President Donald Trump during a joint press conference in London. They discussed various topics, including the special relationship between the two countries, their cooperation on security and military operations, their economic relationship, Brexit, and the possibility of a trade deal. President Trump also addressed his views on the Mayor of London and the ongoing issue of immigration from Mexico. Overall, both leaders expressed their commitment to the alliance between the UK and the US and their willingness to work together on various issues.